::: explanation

The flow retrieves an RSS feed and for each entry, it generates a node in a new flow tab.

The node generated is a comment node with a link in the info box.

For using the <a class="ahl-node-only" data-ids="14a1e43f96d750a4">TriggerImport node</a>, its important to have valid nodes. The nodes generated in the <a class="ahl-node-only" data-ids="77a3c9b5811260e2">function node</a> have the format:

```javascript
msg.payload = {
    "id": msg.payload.id[0].match(/.{16}$/)[0],
    "type": "comment",
    "name": msg.payload.title[0]["_"],
    "info": msg.payload.id[0],
    "x": 801 * Math.random(),
    "y": 699 * Math.random(),
    "wires": [
        []
    ]
}
```

The `id` (in this case) assumes that the orignal RSS id contains a 16 digit hexdecimal. This is an assumption that **only** works with this RSS feed.

